Key Match Events: Hungary threatened the Bosnian goal multiple times but were unable to score.
Bosnian goalkeeper Nikola Vasilj made a series of impressive saves to keep the match goalless.
Dominik Szoboszlai hit the crossbar with a free kick.
Martin Ádám's header was denied by Nikola Vasilj.
Pre-Game Insights: Head coach Marco Rossi made several changes to the starting eleven compared to the previous game against Germany.
Dénes Dibusz replaced Péter Gulácsi in goal.
Endre Botka, Zsolt Nagy, Tamás Nikitscher, and Bendegúz Bolla were included in the starting lineup.
Post-Match Reflections: Hungary captain Dominik Szoboszlai commented that it felt like there were three people in the Bosnian goal.
Fans were not impressed with Hungary's performance, as evidenced by jeers and whistles after the game.
Marco Rossi has had rough periods with the team before but has always managed to come back.
